DESCRIPTION
  The declare builtin, also spelled typeset, declares variables and sets their
  attributes. A plus before a letter removes the attribute where the removal is
  backed, the +i form. In bash mode it backs the array and associative types.

SYNOPSIS
  declare [-aAfFgilnprtux] [+i] [name[=value] ...]

OPTIONS
      --help              Display help.
  -a                      Declare an indexed array.
  -A                      Declare an associative array.
  -f                      Restrict to functions and print their recorded
                          definitions.
  -F                      Print only the names of defined functions, existence
                          by status.
  -g                      Accepted without effect.
  -i                      Mark an integer whose every assignment evaluates as
                          arithmetic, removed by +i.
  -l                      Accepted without effect.
  -n                      Accepted without effect.
  -p                      Print the matching declarations.
  -r                      Accepted without effect.
  -t                      Accepted without effect.
  -u                      Accepted without effect.
  -x                      Mark the variable for the environment.
rc=0
